\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1.1}{\ignorespaces Diagram showing the lifecycle of Antarctic sea ice as observed using remote sensing based on \textcite {barber2005microwave}. The cycle begins with the congealing of the ocean surface known as Freeze Up with peak ice formation during Winter, the second half of the cycle is characterised by various stages of melt with complete sea ice retreat occurring in the Summer.\relax }}{2}{figure.caption.8}%
